news.title: Three land officials behind 254 fraudulent registries in Gurugram's Farrukhnagar
news.para: A probe uncovered that two tehsildars and a naib tehsildar in Farrukhanagar allegedly facilitated 254 fraudulent land registries over four months, converting agricultural land into urban plots and authorizing illegal colonies. The officials manipulated property IDs and used forged documents, potentially costing the state exchequer crores. An investigation is underway in other tehsils as well.

news.title: Nashik: Land records department to conduct ‘Bhumi Adalat’
news.para: The land records department in Nashik division is set to conduct a 'Bhumi Adalat' on October 1st to resolve land disputes amicably. Deputy Director Mahesh Ingale aims to counsel complainants and respondents, addressing issues like mutation entries and land measurements.

news.title: Unauthorised structural alterations rampant at Gurugram's Garden Estate, RWA told to step up checks
news.para: Gurugram's DTCP has issued a notice to the Garden Estate RWA in Sector 24 due to unauthorized structural changes by homeowners. Inspections revealed residents modified units without approvals, violating society rules. The RWA is directed to monitor and report such activities, facing legal action for non-compliance, while residents debate the strictness of the measures.

news.title: Telangana plans amendments to stamp & registration act
news.para: The Telangana government is planning amendments to the Indian Stamp Act and the Registration Act to address revenue losses from auctioned properties and fraudulent registrations. Buyers of auctioned properties may soon be required to pay stamp duty on transaction value.

news.title: Prayagraj development agency gets 63,000 applications for homes under PMAY
news.para: Prayagraj is set to offer homes to 1.2 lakh residents under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana. Over 63,000 people have already applied. Screening is underway, with 70% of applications approved so far. Besides DUDA, PDA and Housing Development Board are also involved. Nav Prayagam Township will house over 45,000 people.

news.title: Bombay HC pulls EOW officials over abuse of 'power of arrest'
news.para: The Bombay High Court has granted interim bail to Mamta Digvijay Singh, criticizing the Economic Offences Wing (EOW) for abusing its power of arrest. The court questioned the timing of Singh's arrest, nearly three months after her statement was recorded, especially as it coincided with her child's birthday.

news.title: Telangana govt to acquire L&T's stake in Hyderabad Metro Rail project for ₹2000 crore
news.para: The Telangana government has agreed to take over Phase-I of the Hyderabad Metro Rail project from L&T Group for ₹2,000 crore, also assuming the company's ₹13,000 crore debt. L&T, holding 90% equity, sought to offload its stake due to operational losses.

news.title: Saudi Arabia freezes rent hikes in Riyadh for five years amid price surge
news.para: Saudi Arabia has initiated a five-year rental price freeze in Riyadh for both residential and commercial properties in response to rising costs fueled by the kingdom's Vision 2030 plan. Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman ordered the freeze to stabilize prices amidst significant infrastructure investments and increased demand.

news.title: Hong Kong lawmakers pass bill to ban substandard tiny apartments
news.para: Hong Kong lawmakers have approved a bill establishing minimum standards for subdivided apartments, impacting approximately 220,000 residents. The new law mandates a minimum size of 8 square meters, a private bathroom, and other essential features. Landlords face fines and imprisonment for non-compliance, aiming to improve living conditions, though concerns arise about potential rent increases and displacement for low-income residents.

news.title: Insomniacs partners with Salesforce to launch India’s largest AI-ready real estate tech ecosystem with 14 products across residential, commercial & redevelopment
news.para: Insomniacs, a leading real estate marketing and technology firm in India, has partnered with Salesforce to introduce an AI-ready suite of digital solutions for the real estate sector. This collaboration aims to provide developers with faster implementation, cost-effectiveness, and deep domain expertise.

news.title: Greater Patna to be developed on NCR model; metro rail operations to begin this month, says minister
news.para: Bihar is set for urban expansion with Greater Patna mirroring Delhi's NCR through land pooling, announced Minister Jibesh Mishra. The Patna Metro's priority corridor is slated for inauguration this month, potentially by PM Modi. Nine satellite towns are planned to decongest cities, alongside efforts to achieve garbage-free urban areas by 2027.

news.title: SC dismisses ED appeal in sand mining case in Tamil Nadu
news.para: The Supreme Court supported the Madras High Court's decision. It stopped the Enforcement Directorate's (ED) investigation. The case involved a suspected sand mining scam in Tamil Nadu. The ED had seized properties. The court said the ED needed a solid case. It needed proof of a crime before acting under the PMLA. The ED's actions were deemed baseless.

news.title: CapitaLand India Trust divest CyberVale and CyberPearl for ₹11,031 million
news.para: CapitaLand India Trust (CLINT) is set to divest CyberVale in Chennai and CyberPearl in Hyderabad for ₹11,031 million. This strategic move, at a 3% premium to valuation, aims to optimize CLINT’s portfolio. The proceeds will be used for debt repayment, reinvestment in higher-yielding projects, and enhanced distributions to unitholders, reducing CLINT's total completed floor area to ~21.2 million sq ft.

news.title: Jharkhand HC refuses to vacate stay on allocation of sand ghats in state
news.para: The Jharkhand High Court has refused to lift the stay on sand ghat allocations, directing Adivasi Buddhijivi Manch to respond to the state government's plea. This decision follows a contempt petition filed by the Manch, alleging non-compliance with the Panchayat Extension of Scheduled Areas (PESA) Act.

news.title: Prime Offices Fund acquires 2.4 million sq ft office space in Chennai for ₹2,550 crore
news.para: Nuvama and Cushman & Wakefield Management's PRIME Offices Fund has acquired a 2.4 million sq ft office campus in Porur, Chennai, from Keppel's real estate division. The transaction, valued at approximately ₹2,550 crore, involves a 100% buyout.

news.title: Punjab cabinet nod to collect charges for lands village land encroachments
news.para: The Punjab cabinet has approved measures to claim charges for illegally occupied village common lands, empowering authorities to collect payments from encroachers, shared between local bodies and the state. Amendments to the Right to Business Act will expedite approvals for industries, while a special NIA court in Mohali aims to accelerate trial proceedings.

news.title: Bombay HC appoints architects to look at structural damage complaints in SRA project in Dharavi
news.para: Bombay High Court intervened in a dispute over construction near Dharavi. Residents of Kamraj Nagar building claimed a new project damaged their structure. The court appointed architects to inspect the site. They will assess structural integrity and suggest remedies. The inspection is set for October 1. A report is expected by October 7.

news.title: Greater Bengaluru authority to launch mobile app for e-khata applications
news.para: Bengaluru's Greater Bengaluru Authority is launching a mobile app for e-khata applications, streamlining the process for property owners. The app, expected to be operational soon, allows direct submission of applications with required documents. This initiative aims to enhance accessibility and user-friendliness, building on the existing web application that processes thousands of applications daily.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government restores plot in Noida to GPL Infrabuild, extends zero-period waiver
news.para: The UP government overturned Noida Authority's decision to cancel GPL Infrabuild's plot allotment in Sector 106, citing delayed possession due to an unresolved high-tension power line issue. The state government emphasized that allotments cannot be cancelled if encumbrance-free possession wasn't provided.
